	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Zelex is referring to the well-known NTSC artifacts, and they repeat every three lines of pixels instead of every two. It happens because the NES PPU takes shortcuts in generating the luma and chroma signals at once instead of generating them separately and band-pass filtering the chroma. Nestopia emulates them fairly faithfully by generating the video signal in the same way as the NES and then decoding it as an NTSC TV would.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

