		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">Zelex wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">http://imgur.com/a/JmoTS<br /><br />This problem is pretty universal to bright colors. Probably due to the analog nature of the RF.<br /><br />Net effect is that lines that are supposed to be straight have little jaggies on the side.</div>
<br />It's not exactly 1 pixel wide, but it is an artifact of <span style="text-decoration: underline">all</span> consoles through NTSC composite.
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.chrismcovell.com/gotRGB/screenshots.html">http://www.chrismcovell.com/gotRGB/screenshots.html</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />Some consoles do a better job at cleaning it up / dancing around the problem.

		

