	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In fact this is due to composite (instead of RF). RF is the cause of more intereference on the screen due to sound signal career and other RF perturbation.
<br />
<br />If you ever used S-Video (or even better, RGB), those "dot crawls" are gone. Of course this is not possible with a NES since it directly outputs composite.
<br />
<br />On a side note I find the dot crawls especially noticeable on the PAL NES. They aren't nearly as noticeable on a NTSC NES or a PAL SNES.

		

		</td>
